	ğ—Ÿğ—¼ğ—®ğ—± ğ—•ğ—®ğ—¹ğ—®ğ—»ğ—°ğ—²ğ—¿: A #loadbbalancer is a device or service that distributes incoming traffic across multiple servers to ensure that no single server becomes a bottleneck. Load balancers help to improve the availability, reliability, and scalability of a system by distributing the workload across multiple servers. Load balancing can be performed based on various algorithms, such as round-robin, least connections, and IP hash.

